This paper discusses the efficiency of ontology-mediated querying over relational databases, which is a topic related to database management (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on description logic (DL) ontologies, which are used in ontology engineering and knowledge representation, making categories such as cs.LO and cs.DL likely. Finally, the paper also discusses complexity theory and parameterized complexity, which are topics related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
